3.  Now in StockTradingServiceImpl class we override bulkStockOrder() with request as StockOrder and response as OrderSummary

@Override
    public StreamObserver<StockOrder> bulkStockOrder(StreamObserver<OrderSummary> responseObserver) {

        //build responseobserver
        return new StreamObserver<StockOrder>() {

            private int totalOrders = 0;
            private double totalAmount = 0;
            private int successCount = 0;

            //Every request coming from client this onnext() will execute and we need to map these value results.
            @Override
            public void onNext(StockOrder stockOrder) {
                //every time this method execute total order increase it one by one
                totalOrders++;
                totalAmount += stockOrder.getPrice() * stockOrder.getQuantity();
                successCount++;
                System.out.println("Received order : " + stockOrder);
            }

            //execute when there will be any failure
            @Override
            public void onError(Throwable throwable) {
                System.out.println("Server unable to process the request : "+throwable.getMessage());
            }

            //when everything is completed then oncomplete will give the acknowledge to
the client and here we need to build your ordersummary response 
            @Override
            public void onCompleted() {
                OrderSummary summary = OrderSummary.newBuilder()
                        .setTotalOrders(totalOrders)
                        .setSuccessCount(successCount)
                        .setTotalAmount(totalAmount)
                        .build();
                //send ordersummary from your server to the client
                responseObserver.onNext(summary);
                responseObserver.onCompleted();

            }
        };

    }

So from client you will get n number of request, we are evalating each and every field and then at the end we are sending. Once everything is completed then oncomplete method will execute and we are building the order summary. Once we build the summary result we are sending it back to the request user or client.

