Springboot + gRPC Bidirectional Streaming
    In birectional streaming, imagine the client and server are both in a conversation like a WhatsApp chat. For example, client sends stock symbol one by one and the server keep responding in real time with updates. Now if you observe client and server sends and receive stream of data
at the same time without blocking each other, here no one waits for the others to finish. Client will keep sending the request and server will keep giving you the response back. 

1. In server appl, we add rpc method liveTrading in proto file with input as StockOrder and output as TradeStatus, so we create message for TradeStatus. Here client will send stream of stockorder request and the server will keep sending the tradestatus update. 

service StockTradingService{

  // UNARY - RPC -> get current stock price
  rpc getStockPrice(StockRequest) returns (StockResponse);

  //server streaming
  rpc subscribeStockPrice(StockRequest) returns (stream StockResponse);

  //Client streaming - place multiple stock orders
  rpc bulkStockOrder(stream StockOrder) returns (OrderSummary);

  //Bidirectional streaming - live trading.
  rpc liveTrading(stream StockOrder) returns (stream TradeStatus);

}

message TradeStatus {
  string order_id = 1;
  string status = 2; // e.g., "EXECUTED", "FAILED", "PENDING"
  string message = 3; // reason if failed or success message
  string timestamp = 4;
}

