 @Override
    public StreamObserver<Book> getExpensiveBook(StreamObserver<Book> responseObserver) {

     //we have to return the streamobserver of books because the client will send multiple books to the server
        return new StreamObserver<Book>() {

 //we have to find the expensive book so we initialize Book=null and also keep a pricetrack variable since we're gonna get many books.
            Book expensiveBook = null;
            float priceTrack = 0;

           //whenever the client will send multiple book, each book will be coming into onnext() 
 //Now we will check the book which the client is sending, we get the prize of that book and if it's greater than the pricetrack, we update expensivebook as a book
            @Override
            public void onNext(Book book) {
                if (book.getPrice() > priceTrack) {
                    priceTrack = book.getPrice();
                    expensiveBook = book;
                }
            }

           //send the error using onerror
            @Override
            public void onError(Throwable throwable) {
                responseObserver.onError(throwable);
            }

       //when all the books has been consumed by onnext and oncompleted would be called and we will again call onnext because since the server has to send one book
            @Override
            public void onCompleted() {
                responseObserver.onNext(expensiveBook);
                responseObserver.onCompleted();
            }
        };
    }

So first all the books will be consumed by onnext method and when client will send acknowledgement that all the books has been sent by the client then the server oncompleted method will be invoked and here to send that expensive book we have to call the responseobserver onnext method and pass the expensive book so that client will receive that book

