gRPC Microservice with using Interceptor based JWT authentication with Springboot 4.0.1 and spring grpc version 1.0.2
    Interceptor‑based JWT auth means JWT authentication and authorization are enforced by a gRPC ServerInterceptor, before the request reaches any gRPC service method.
In simple words, every gRPC call passes through an interceptor → JWT is validated there → only then the call reaches your service logic.

Request flow (visual)
grpc client (grpcurl / app)
        │
        ▼
 gRPC ServerInterceptor  ✅  ← JWT validation happens HERE
        │
        ▼
 gRPC Service Method     ✅  ← business logic

If JWT is missing / invalid / unauthorized, the request never reaches your service.

Interceptor‑based JWT vs REST filter‑based JWT
REST                                 gRPC
Servlet Filter                    ServerInterceptor 
HTTP headers                      Metadata 
SecurityContext                   gRPC Context 
Controller executes after filter  Service executes after interceptor 

✅ Why Spring Security is NOT used here
In Spring gRPC 1.0.2:

❌ No @PreAuthorize
❌ No SecurityFilterChain
❌ No GrpcSecurityMetadataSource

So:
✅ Interceptor‑based JWT is the ONLY supported, correct approach


