client, the data could have the customer data or there could be a custom error as well, so the client have to  write a switch statement to decide if it is a custom error then what action needs to be taken and when the data is customer then what action needs to be taken.

- Generate the java classes using mvn clean install

2. Create implementation of getCustomers in CustomerService class
 create a range from 1 to 10 using IntStream and for each number we check if it is not even then create a customerdetails object and then set the customerror and if it is even we set customerdetails 

@Override
    public void getCustomers(Empty request, StreamObserver<CustomerDetails> responseObserver) {
    	//create a range from 1 to 10 using IntStream
    	IntStream.range(1, 10)
    	         .forEach(number -> {
    	        	 //we check if it is not even then create a customerdetails object and then set the customerror
    	        	 if(!(number%2==0)) {
    	        		 CustomerDetails notfound=CustomerDetails.newBuilder()
    	        		      .setCustomError(CustomError.newBuilder()
    	        		    		      .setErrorType("NOT_FOUND")
    	        		    		      .setMessage(String.format("Customer with id:%d not found",number)).build())
    	        		      .build();
    	        		 //since we are treating the error as a data we send to onnext
    	        		 responseObserver.onNext(notfound); 
    	       } //if it is even we set customerdetails 
    	        	 else {
    	        		 CustomerDetails customer=CustomerDetails.newBuilder()
	        		      .setCustomer(Customer.newBuilder()
	                              .setName("Ram")
	                              .setEmail("ram@gmail.com")
	                              .build())
	        		      .build();
    	        		 responseObserver.onNext(customer);
    	        	 }
    	         });
    	responseObserver.onCompleted();
    }

